record_data.record_plain_text: NEWARK ENERGY CENTER, LLC REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE Newark Energy Center, LLC ("NEC") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from an electric generation facility located in Newark, New Jersey ("Facility") that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth NEC's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the Facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on September 21, 2015. REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT: TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The total annual revenue requirement is $1,950,000. The total monthly revenue requirement is $1,950,000 / 12 = $162,500. 01
record_data.filing_title: Motion for Interim Rates of Newark Energy Center
